    • Method Detail

      • bEndpointAddress

        public int bEndpointAddress()
        Returns the endpoint address. The address is encoded as follows:
        • Bit 7: The direction (ignored by control endpoints), 0=OUT, 1=IN
        • Bit 6-4: Reserved
        • Bit 3-0: The endpoint number.
        Returns:
        The endpoint address (unsigned byte).

      • bmAttributes

        public int bmAttributes()
        Returns the endpoint attributes. This is a bitmask with the following meaning:
        • Bit 7-6: Reserved
        • Bit 5-4: Usage type (00=Data endpoint, 01=Feedback endpoint, 10=Implicit feedback data endpoint, 11=Reserved)
        • Bit 3-2: Synchronization type (00=No synchronization, 01=Asynchronous, 10=Adaptive, 11=Synchronous)
        • Bit 1-0: Transfer type (00=Control,01=Isochronous,10=Bulk,11=Interrupt). See USB_ENDPOINT_TYPE_* constants.
        Returns:
        The endpoint attributes bitmask (unsigned byte).

      • wMaxPacketSize

        public int wMaxPacketSize()
        Returns the maximum packet size the endpoint is capable of sending or receiving when this configuration is selected. For all endpoints this maximum packet size is located in bits 10-0. Bits 12-11 specify the number of additional opportunities per microframe: 00=None (1 Transaction per microframe), 01=1 additional (2 per microframe), 10=2 additional (3 per microframe), 11=Reserved. Bits 15-13 are reserved.
        Returns:
        The maximum packet size of the endpoint (unsigned short).

      • bInterval

        public int bInterval()
        Returns the interval for polling endpoint for data transfers in frames or microframes depending on the device operating speed.
        Returns:
        The interval for polling endpoint (unsigned byte).

      • bRefresh

        Returns:
